<HEADLINE> Markets Closed in London / British Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Financial markets were closed in London Monday for  
a national holiday. 
</P>
<P>
	Share prices rose Friday on the London Stock Exchange.  
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-Share Index finished up  
26.70 points, or 0.4 percent, at 6,226.20, having traded in a range 
between 6,110.10 and 6,229.10. 
</P>
<P>
	Provisional volume was 840 million shares compared with 1  
billion shares on Thursday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
