<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Rain fell today across the southern Plains, parts of the Midwest  
and the Rockies, while it was beach and barbecue weather in the 
East. 
</P>
<P>
	The temperatures crept toward the 90-degree mark in most of the  
major cities in the Northeast, and clear skies stretched from Maine 
to Florida. The West Coast saw fair and pleasant weather. 
</P>
<P>
	Heavy rains, wind and thunderstorms drenched northeastern Texas  
and parts of Louisiana and Arkansas, while less intense rains fell 
in the Great Lakes and Ohio Valley. In Midland, Mich., strong winds 
uprooted trees and damaged the roof of a hotel convention center. 
</P>
<P>
	There were scattered showers in Kentucky, Tennessee, Mississippi  
and Alabama. 
</P>
<P>
	Wyoming, Utah and Colorado also saw widely scattered showers and  
thunderstorms, but the rest of the western United States saw clear 
skies and warm temperatures. 
</P>
<P>
	The high temperature in the lower 48 states was 102 degrees at  
Laughlin Air Force Base, Texas. The low was 17 degrees at Cody, 
Wyo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
