<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Girl Killed in New York Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A 3-year-old girl was shot to death on a street  
corner early today. Police said the bullet may have been intended 
for her father. 
</P>
<P>
	Iris Turull was with her father, Ruben Turull, on a crowded  
street corner a half block from their home in the Bronx just after 
midnight. Four to six shots were fired from a white minivan, said 
Deputy Inspector Michael Oveis. Iris was hit in the head and died a 
few hours later. 
</P>
<P>
	Turull, 38, may have been involved in a fight near the family's  
home over the weekend, Oveis said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We think the people involved in that dispute may have come  
back,'' Oveis said. ``I don't think the girl was the intended 
target.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Flowers, candles and stuffed animals were placed near the spot  
where Iris died. 
</P>
<P>
	``You couldn't ask for no more sweeter than Iris,'' said  
Patricia Holloway, who lives across the hall from the Turulls. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
