<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Six Die in Crash on Penn. Turnpike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BEDFORD, Pa. (AP) -- Five young Amish people and their hired  
driver were killed early today when their van crossed a center 
divider on the Pennsylvania Turnpike and plowed into a 
tractor-trailer. 
</P>
<P>
	A seventh person in the van was in critical condition, and the  
truck driver was hospitalized with ``moderate injuries,'' state 
police Cpl. John Cypress said. 
</P>
<P>
	The van was traveling westbound on the turnpike 84 miles  
southeast of Pittsburgh. The driver lost control, hit the divider, 
and then crossed an emergency opening into the eastbound lane, 
Cypress said. 
</P>
<P>
	Three people were thrown from the van as it collided with the  
truck and burst into flames, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Killed were two pairs of sisters whose ages ranged from 16 to  
20, an Amish man who has not been identified, and the group's 
40-year-old driver. 
</P>
<P>
	The Amish usually hire drivers for long trips because their  
religious beliefs discourage driving automobiles. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
