<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CD-ROM Teaches Kids Anatomy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Whether it's a fresh-from-the-factory model or a 50-something  
model with more than a few dents, the human body is an amazing 
machine, and understanding it is an important part of 
elementary-level education. 
</P>
<P>
	DK Interactive Learning has a CD-ROM aimed at 6- to 10-year-olds  
that's worth a look. My Amazing Human Body runs on both IBM and Mac 
platforms and presents human anatomy in an entertaining and 
instructive way. 
</P>
<P>
	The star of My Amazing Human Body is Seemore Skinless, a chatty  
skeleton with multicolored internal organs, and the CD-ROM offers 
six main areas. 
</P>
<P>
	``Take Me Apart'' allows the child to explode and reassemble  
Seemore's body using drag-and-drop with the mouse. It helps build 
an overview of what's where, and won't let the user put a kidney 
where an eyeball is required. 
</P>
<P>
	``What Am I Made Of?'' allows children to zero in on specific  
body parts, delivering anatomical factoids and offering rotated and 
x-ray views, as well as a ``poke'' function and measurements. DK 
Interactive Learning handles the differences between male and 
female by ignoring them -- Seemore has no genitalia or sexual 
characteristics of any sort. 
</P>
<P>
	``Build Me A Body'' is a game in which answering questions earns  
you body parts. When the body is complete, the child can name it 
and ``photograph'' it. 
</P>
<P>
	And in ``Me and My Day,'' the user takes Seemore through a  
typical day, using an interactive control panel to monitor and 
fulfill the body's needs for rest, food and drink and activity. 
</P>
<P>
	Finally, a ``Secret File'' section allows the recording of diary  
and personal information and an Information Section allows 
topic-oriented investigation and searching. 
</P>
<P>
	The illustrations throughout are clear and the text of the  
explanations of various anatomical functions is also read aloud, 
which will help some younger users get over the big words. 
Animations are smooth and amusing. The CD-ROM is required to run 
the software. 
</P>
<P>
	Installation was smooth and included an uninstall program.  
</P>
<P>
	System requirements for the PC are Windows 95 or 98, at least a  
486DX2 66-megahertz CPU, 12 megabytes of RAM and 26 megabytes of 
hard disk space. For the Mac, System 7.1.2 or better, and at least 
a 33-megahertz 68LC040 and eight megabytes of RAM (12 for System 
7.5.3 and higher, plus Power PC) and six megabytes of disk space. 
</P>
<P>
	DK Interactive Learning products are available at retail and  
over the web at http://www.dk.com. The web price is $29.95. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	Questions and comments are welcome. E-mail via the Internet to  
lblasko(at)ap.org, or send regular mail to Larry Blasko, AP, 50 
Rockefeller Plaza, New York, NY 10020. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
