<HEADLINE> One Rafter Dead in Montana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DIVIDE, Mont. (AP) -- Rescue workers today searched for a woman  
believed to have died in a weekend rafting accident that killed one 
of her companions. 
</P>
<P>
	Four people were on a raft that went over a dam and capsized  
Sunday in the Big Hole River in southwestern Montana. Sandra 
Townsend, 48, drowned, and Roxie Oaks, 22, was presumed dead. Miss 
Oaks' fiance and another man survived. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheriff John McPherson said that if Miss Oaks hadn't drowned,  
she probably would have died from hypothermia in the frigid river, 
which was swollen by snowmelt and recent rains. More than 60 
searchers found no trace of her on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	One of the survivors told authorities the current prevented the  
party from guiding the raft to the riverbank while approaching the 
dam. 
  	   	
</P>
