<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Breakdown by Region of Travel Poll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A look at results of an Associated Press poll on travel by  
region: 

</P>
<P>
	 *NORTHEAST   	
</P>
<P>
	Just about half in the Northeast travel by car on vacation and  
four-out-of-10 travel by plane, more than the people in the South 
and North Central regions, but about the same as the West. A 
quarter of the people living in the Northeast say they will spend 
$3,000 or more on vacations this year. 

</P>
<P>
	 *NORTH CENTRAL   	
</P>
<P>
	Almost half of the people from this region said they would spend  
between $500 and $1,500 on vacation. More than half say they will 
travel by car and about three out of 10 say they plan to fly. 

</P>
<P>
	 *SOUTH   	
</P>
<P>
	Almost two-thirds of Southerners travel by car when on vacation,  
the highest percentage of any region. More than a quarter expect to 
take their longest vacation for less than a week, while almost half 
will take a week. A third of the people in the South say they will 
spend $500 or less on vacation, the most in any region who plan to 
spend that amount. 

</P>
<P>
	 *WEST    	
</P>
<P>
	Four out of 10 say they plan to fly on vacation. A fourth say  
they will vacation for at least two weeks and a fifth of the 
Westerners said they will vacation for three weeks or more. That is 
twice as many as the number of Southerners who said they will 
vacation for three weeks or more. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
