<HEADLINE> Filly Beats Boys at Churchill Downs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Trainer Bob Baffert, who will try to beat  
males with the filly Silverbulletday in the Belmont Stakes, did it 
Monday at Churchill Downs with the filly Chilukki. 
</P>
<P>
	Chilukki beat six males in winning the $171,750 Kentucky  
Breeders' Cup for 2-year-olds by 4 3/4 lengths. She raced the 5 1/2 
furlongs in 1:04, two-fifths of a second off the track record in 
scoring her second victory in her second start. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
