<HEADLINE> Soaring Softly Wins Belmont Feature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Soaring Softly drew away from her rivals through  
the stretch to register a decisive 5 1/2-length victory in Belmont 
Park's Monday feature, the 41st running of the $150,000, Grade II 
Sheepshead Bay Handicap for fillies and mares 3-and-older. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old filly cruised through the final furlong to cover  
1 3/8 miles in 2:15 over the turf for her fourth straight victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Starry Dreamer was second in the six-horse field. With Pinafore  
Park another three-quarter lengths behind. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the second winning ride for Mike Smith in the last three  
Sheepshead Bays. He took the 1997 running aboard Maxzene. 
</P>
<P>
	Soaring Softly earned $90,000 for Joan and John W. Phillips and  
returned $7.80, $4.40 and $3.90. Starry Dreamer paid $4.80 and 
$4.40 and Pinafore Park was $6.40 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
