<HEADLINE> Dollar mixed in European Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold prices were higher in 
Zurich. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0481, up from $1.0473 Friday. The  
dollar was quoted at 121.47 Japanese yen, up from 120.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates, compared with late Friday: 1.5216 Swiss  
francs, up from 1.5212; 1.4743 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4734. 
The British pound was quoted at $1.6043, down from $1.6018. 
</P>
<P>
	Markets were closed in London for a holiday, but other European  
markets were open. New York trading was closed for the Memorial Day 
holiday. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth: 1.8661 German marks, down from 1.8675; 
6.2585 French francs, down from 6.2633; 2.1026 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.1042; 1,847.41 Italian lire, down from 1,848.82. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich, the gold price was $269.95 bid, up from $269.35.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell 10 cents in Hong Kong to $270.15.  
  	   	
</P>
